(# Login Security Fix Summary) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Date: May 5, 2026) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## What Was Happening) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The browser was showing a Supabase OAuth callback URL with `#access_token=...` in the address) Tj
T*
(bar. That is the implicit OAuth flow. It can happen when Google/Supabase redirects back to the) Tj
T*
(app but the app is not running, has not mounted yet, or fails before the auth callback cleanup) Tj
T*
(code runs.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Any URL containing `access_token`, `refresh_token`, or `provider_token` should be treated as) Tj
T*
(sensitive. Do not share it. If one has been exposed, sign out of that account or revoke the) Tj
T*
(session in Supabase.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## What Was Fixed) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The app now scrubs OAuth callback parameters before React renders.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Added:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- `src/lib/authCallback.ts`) Tj
T*
(- early callback cleanup in `src/main.tsx`) Tj
T*
(- callback parameter consumption in `src/context/AuthContext.tsx`) Tj
T*
(- PKCE auth configuration in `src/lib/supabase.ts`) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The early cleanup stores callback parameters briefly in `sessionStorage`, removes token-bearing) Tj
T*
(values from the visible URL, then lets the auth provider complete the Supabase session exchange.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Why PKCE Matters) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Supabase supports two browser auth callback styles:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- implicit flow: returns tokens in the URL fragment, such as `#access_token=...`) Tj
T*
(- PKCE flow: returns a short `?code=...` that the app exchanges for a session) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The app is now configured for PKCE:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(```ts) Tj
T*
(auth: {) Tj
T*
(  detectSessionInUrl: true,) Tj
T*
(  flowType: "pkce",) Tj
T*
(  persistSession: true,) Tj
T*
(  autoRefreshToken: true) Tj
T*
(}) Tj
T*
(```) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This reduces token exposure in future redirects.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
